adGenAOSFanMib.name: adGenAOSFanMib

revisions.description: Created the adGenAosFan MIB. Revision R10.11

adGenAOSFanMib.contactinfo: Technical Support Dept. Postal: ADTRAN, Inc. 901 Explorer Blvd. Huntsville, AL 35806 Tel: +1 800 726-8663 Fax: +1 256 963 6217 E-mail: support@adtran.com
adGenAOSFanMib.description: The MIB module defines fan configuration information and traps for AdtranOS products.

adGenAOSFanTrapEnable.name: adGenAOSFanTrapEnable
adGenAOSFanTrapEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the system produces the fan failure trap.

adGenAOSFanNumber.name: adGenAOSFanNumber
adGenAOSFanNumber.description: A numerical representation of the chassis's fan.

adGenAOSFanFailure.name: adGenAOSFanFailure
adGenAOSFanFailure.description: A fan failure trap signifies that one of the fans inside the chassis has failed.

adGenAOSFanFailureResume.name: adGenAOSFanFailureResume
adGenAOSFanFailureResume.description: A fan failure Resume trap signifies that one of the fans inside the chassis has recoverd the failure.

adGenAOSFanFullCompliance.name: adGenAOSFanFullCompliance
adGenAOSFanFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement version 2 of the adGenAosFan MIB. When this MIB is implemented with support for read-write, then such an implementation can claim full compliance.

adGenAOSFanTrapCfgGroup.name: adGenAOSFanTrapCfgGroup
adGenAOSFanTrapCfgGroup.description: This group contains the objects necessary to enable/disable fan failure traps.

adGenAOSFanTrapGroup.name: adGenAOSFanTrapGroup
adGenAOSFanTrapGroup.description: The objects necessary to control fan notification messages.

adGenAOSFanNotificationGroup.name: adGenAOSFanNotificationGroup
adGenAOSFanNotificationGroup.description: Traps which may be used to enhance event driven management of the chassis's fan.
